oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Dennis E. Kearney
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This photograph of Dennis E. Kearney shows him in uniform, with his hat raised in his right hand and a large cigar in his left. It was probably taken at his home in Memphis, Tennessee just prior to his shipping out. Kearney started his service in Btry. B, 115th FA, 30th Div. at Camp Sevier, Greenville, S.C. Kearney had also served along the U.S.-Mexican border in 1916-1917 as part of the Tenn. National Guard in attempt to capture Pancho Villa.
